tonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104saj1665703274216.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/saj1665703274216.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/saj1665703274216.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"saj1665703274216\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      /tfo\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Record keystrokes in a Uniface application running in character mode to an ASCII file. </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"saj1665703274216__section_w2958ab1b5b1_w2959ab1b5_w2960ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"saj1665703274216__p_d151436e1_d151437e1_d151438e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/tfo</span>{<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>}</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"saj1665703274216__section_w2961ab1b5b3_w2962ab1b5_w2963ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d390586e66\">\n                  \n Arguments\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"saj1665703274216__p_d151442e1_d151443e1_d151444e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>—optional file name; maximum of 12 characters. Letters, digits, and underscores (_) are allowed; the first character must be a letter. If no name is given, the <var class=\"keyword varname\">Shell</var>\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">.tfo</span> is used. If no extension is specified, <span class=\"ph filepath\">.tfo</span> (Test File Output) is assumed.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"saj1665703274216__section_w2964ab1b5b5_w2965ab1b5_w2966ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d390586e87\">\n                  \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"saj1665703274216__p_d151448e1_d151449e1_d151450e1\">Record all the keystrokes used in a Uniface application in an ASCII file. Only keystrokes are recorded in the TFO file. Mouse movement and clicks are not recorded.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"saj1665703274216__p_d151451e1_d151452e1_d151453e1\">When you use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/tfo</span> switch, a copy of all output which normally occurs on the message line also occurs in the message frame.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"saj1665703274216__p_d151454e1_d151455e1_d151456e1\">The recorded file can be played back with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/tfi</span> switch to reproduce the session exactly as it was recorded, with the keyboard input coming from a file instead of the keyboard.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"saj1665703274216__note_w2967ab1b5b5b9_w2968ab1b5b5_w2969ab1b5_w2970ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The application must be running in\n      character mode (that is, <code class=\"ph codeph\">$GUI=$CHR</code>).</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/swq1665703274088.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/tfi</a><p>Play back the recorded keystrokes stored in a test file output file.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531878\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531878\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/tfo Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 /tfo Record keystrokes in a Uniface application running in character mode to an ASCII file. /tfo { = FileName } Arguments FileName —optional file name; maximum of 12 characters. Letters, digits, and underscores (_) are allowed; the first character must be a letter. If no name is given, the Shell .tfo is used. If no extension is specified, .tfo (Test File Output) is assumed. Description Record all the keystrokes used in a Uniface application in an ASCII file. Only keystrokes are recorded in the TFO file. Mouse movement and clicks are not recorded. When you use the /tfo switch, a copy of all output which normally occurs on the message line also occurs in the message frame. The recorded file can be played back with the /tfi switch to reproduce the session exactly as it was recorded, with the keyboard input coming from a file instead of the keyboard. Note: The application must be running in character mode (that is, $GUI=$CHR ). Related Links /tfi Play back the recorded keystrokes stored in a test file output file. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}